  "market_context": "On the daily, Wednesday formed a reversal and Thursday continued, closing outside Wednesday's range, giving a bullish bias targeting Thursday's high / previous day high. Price was respecting the prior day's EQ and T-spot, setting up Friday continuation.",
  "key_observation": "The 2 AM (London) 4-hour candle made a large opposing run below the prior candle's low, then reversed back into range to form a reversal candle. This sets up the 6–10 AM (New York) candle as the continuation expansion candle to trade higher.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Start top-down on the daily — Wednesday formed a reversal and Thursday continuation closed outside Wednesday's range, so anticipate Friday continuation higher to Thursday's high.",
    "Step 2: Note price is respecting the previous day range's EQ and T-spot, supporting the bullish daily bias.",
    "Step 3: Drop to the 15-minute timeframe paired with the 4-hour candle to find entry within the AMD framework.",
    "Step 4: Identify the 2 AM 4-hour candle as a reversal candle — accumulation early, then a large opposing run (manipulation) below the prior candle's low forming a wick, then a strong close back into range.",
    "Step 5: Anticipate distribution higher in the next 4-hour candle (6–10 AM, New York session) — the continuation expansion candle.",
    "Step 6: On the 15-minute, wait for the wick of 6 AM to form a protected swing — a sweep of a low followed by a close over the series of down-close candles (CISD) inside a fair value gap.",
    "Step 7: Enter long after the protected swing forms, stop below the swept low, target the previous day high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade reached the previous day high target successfully.",
  "lessons": "Let the wick of the higher-timeframe candle form before entering — don't try to catch the wick itself. Align daily bias with the 4-hour reversal/continuation candle profile, then use a 15-minute protected swing for precise entry with tight stop.",
